        public ChannelBuilder setName(java.lang.String name)

        name - The name of the channel.

        ChannelBuilder for chaining.
        Throws:

      • setBitrate

        public ChannelBuilder setBitrate(int bitrate)
        Set the bitrate of this IVoiceChannel. Setting the bitrate will not affect anything if this builder is used to build a ITextChannel.
        Parameters:
        bitrate - The integer bitrate.
        Returns:
        ChannelBuilder for chaining.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException -
        • If the bitrate is smaller than 8000.
        • The bitrate is greater than 128000. Note that the builder does not knows if the guild this channel will be created in is VIP or not, so the limit here is for VIP. You must check if the guild is vip or not, otherwise there might be exception thrown when creating a channel via this builder.
        See Also:
        IVoiceChannel.getBitrate()

      • setUserLimit

        public ChannelBuilder setUserLimit(int userLimit)
        Set the user limit of this IVoiceChannel. Setting the user limit will not affect anything if this builder is used to build a ITextChannel.
        Parameters:
        userLimit - The user limit.
        Returns:
        ChannelBuilder for chaining.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the bitrate is smaller than 0 or greater than 99.
        See Also:
        IVoiceChannel.getUserLimit()
